---
title: Garlicky Shrimp Scampi with Bell Peppers and Linguine
description: Once upon a time, way before seafood buffets existed, there was an Italian predecessor of this dish that featured scampi, lobster-like creatures that we know as langoustines. It was only after immigrants brought it over to America that shrimp were swapped in and tacked on to the name. We’re shaking things up once again, adding in red bell peppers. They not only provide a veggie boost, but also a natural sweetness that cuts through the buttery richness and garlicky funk.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/lemony-shrimp-linguine-w52-famil-d413c0bf.jpg
